SIMPLE: weird
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Weird
<hw>Weird</hw> <pr>(w⟦emac⟧rd)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>wirde</ets>, <ets>werde</ets>, AS. <ets>wyrd</ets> fate, fortune,
one of the Fates, fr. <ets>weor⟦edh⟧an</ets> to be, to become; akin to
OS. <ets>wurd</ets> fate, OHG. <ets>wurt</ets>, Icel.
<ets>ur⟦edh⟧r</ets>. ⟦root⟧143. See <er>Worth</er> to become.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Fate; destiny; one of the Fates, or Norns; also, a
prediction.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A spell or charm.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Scot.]</mark>
<rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weird</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Weird
<hw>Weird</hw>, <pos>a.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to fate; concerned with
destiny.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to witchcraft; caused by, or
suggesting, magical influence; supernatural; unearthly; wild; <as>as, a
<ex>weird</ex> appearance, look, sound, etc</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Myself too had <qex>weird</qex> seizures.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Those sweet, low tones, that seemed like a <qex>weird</qex>
incantation.</q> <rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Weird sisters</b></col>, <cd>the Fates.</cd>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark> <rj><au>G. Douglas.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Shakespeare uses the term for the three witches in
Macbeth.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>weird sisters</qex>, hand in hand,⟦br⟧
Posters of the sea and land.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weird</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Weird
<hw>Weird</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To foretell the fate of; to
predict; to destine to.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>
<rj><au>Jamieson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weirdness</ent>⟦br⟧
